item.description:
Need to quickly setup ssl and default to that for our sites.
This article made it simple stupid for getting the certs setup.
Then I wrapped up the redirect as seen below
server {
listen 80;
listen 443 ssl;
server_name somesite-dev.stagingarea.info;
root /home/someuser/somesite-dev.stagingarea.info/public;
ssl on;
ssl_certificate /etc/nginx/ssl/nginx.crt;
ssl_certificate_key /etc/nginx/ssl/nginx.key;
# Prevent a look
if ($ssl_protocol = &quot;&quot;) {
rewrite ^ https://$server_name$request_uri? permanent;
}
index index.html index.htm index.php;
charset utf-8;
}
Thanks to this post as well http://serverfault.
